    <div class="callout-lbl">The Math in Plain English</div>
    <p>You'll invest roughly <strong>$35–65K/year</strong> depending on the phase (rising sharply with dual income and post-daycare). At 7% real annual return over 37 years, with contributions growing as incomes grow, you reliably land in the $3.2–3.8M range. That's not cutting it close — it's a comfortable target with a real margin of safety. The years you spend on travel and experiences don't meaningfully erode the retirement outcome; they add immeasurably to the years you can't get back.</p>
