  <div class="callout sage">
    <div class="callout-lbl">Earlier Kids = Longer Post-Daycare Freedom Window</div>
    <p>By having children before she turns 30, daycare is essentially over by age 35 — giving you <strong>25 years</strong> of post-daycare, dual-income investment time before retirement (vs. 19 years in the previous plan). The earlier "pain" of daycare during the house purchase years is more than compensated by the longer compounding runway afterward. This timing actually works slightly better for wealth building.</p>
