  <div class="philosophy" style="margin-top:32px;padding:36px 44px">
    <div class="philosophy-tag">The Closing Thought</div>
    <p>You don't need $10 million to retire well. You need <strong>enough</strong> — and a life rich enough along the way that you'd be proud of how you spent it. This plan gives you both. A real travel budget. Real dinners out. Kids whose childhood memories include adventures, not just frugality. And at 60, a portfolio that funds everything you need with comfortable margin, plus Social Security as a bonus that makes it even better. <strong>That's not compromise. That's the plan.</strong></p>
